  pattern_paramod: [timeout: 5000, paramodulation_mode: :pattern],
  no_paramod: [timeout: 5000, paramodulation_mode: :matching]
]
```

## Equational chains

The simplest equational problem: a chain of equalities `a₁ = a₂`, `a₂ = a₃`, …
should yield `a₁ = aₙ` by transitive paramodulation. A pure FO prover handles
this in milliseconds; Leibniz expansion has to instantiate `P` once per link.

**Chain of length 3.**

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      thf(a, type, a: $i).
      thf(b, type, b: $i).
      thf(c, type, c: $i).
      thf(ab, axiom, a = b).
      thf(bc, axiom, b = c).
      thf(conj, conjecture, a = c).
      """,
      opts
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

