## Deep functional congruence

`x = y ⇒ f(f(f(x))) = f(f(f(y)))`. The Leibniz blow-up here is severe: the
prover must guess `P := λz. f(f(f(z))) = f(f(f(y)))` (or a witness equivalent),
whereas paramodulation just rewrites `f(f(f(x)))` once.

**Depth 3 over the same constant.**

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      thf(f, type, f: $i>$i).
      thf(conj, conjecture,
        ![X:$i, Y:$i]: ( (X = Y) => (f @ (f @ (f @ X)) = f @ (f @ (f @ Y))) )
      ).
      """,
      opts
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

