## Idempotent semigroup ⇒ commutative

Boolean-ring-style problem: an associative idempotent operation must be
commutative. Pure FO equational, but proof has a small algebraic trick
(use `(x∘y)∘(x∘y) = x∘y`) that paramodulation discovers naturally.

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      thf(o, type, o: $i>$i>$i).
      thf(assoc, axiom,
        ![X:$i, Y:$i, Z:$i]: o @ (o @ X @ Y) @ Z = o @ X @ (o @ Y @ Z)).
      thf(idem, axiom, ![X:$i]: o @ X @ X = X).
      thf(abs_l, axiom, ![X:$i, Y:$i]: o @ X @ (o @ X @ Y) = o @ X @ Y).
      thf(abs_r, axiom, ![X:$i, Y:$i]: o @ (o @ X @ Y) @ Y = o @ X @ Y).
      thf(conj, conjecture, ![X:$i, Y:$i]: o @ X @ Y = o @ Y @ X).
      """,
      Keyword.put(opts, :timeout, 10_000)
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

