## Robinson arithmetic micro-fragment

A textbook successor-arithmetic problem: define `plus` by the usual two
equations, then prove `1+2 = 3`. Paramodulation should evaluate the term
left-to-right; Leibniz blows up because every intermediate term spawns a new
`P` schema instantiation.

```elixir
peano_axioms = """
thf(o_t, type, o: $i).
thf(s_t, type, s: $i>$i).
thf(plus_t, type, plus: $i>$i>$i).
thf(plus_zero, axiom, ![Y:$i]: plus @ o @ Y = Y).
thf(plus_succ, axiom,
  ![X:$i, Y:$i]: plus @ (s @ X) @ Y = s @ (plus @ X @ Y)).
"""
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```
"thf(o_t, type, o: $i).\nthf(s_t, type, s: $i>$i).\nthf(plus_t, type, plus: $i>$i>$i).\nthf(plus_zero, axiom, ![Y:$i]: plus @ o @ Y = Y).\nthf(plus_succ, axiom,\n  ![X:$i, Y:$i]: plus @ (s @ X) @ Y = s @ (plus @ X @ Y)).\n"
```

**`1 + 1 = 2`.**

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      #{peano_axioms}
      thf(conj, conjecture, plus @ (s @ o) @ (s @ o) = s @ (s @ o)).
      """,
      opts
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

```

