**Left-zero is right-zero for closed numerals:** `plus(s(s(o)), o) = s(s(o))`.
This one needs induction in general, but for a _closed_ numeral the rewriter
should hammer it out. A useful gauge of how much the prover slows down with
deeper successor stacks.

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      #{peano_axioms}
      thf(conj, conjecture,
        plus @ (s @ (s @ (s @ o))) @ o = s @ (s @ (s @ (plus @ o @ o)))).
      """,
      opts
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

<!-- livebook:{"output":true} -->

