## Equality interacting with predicates

These are mixed equational/relational problems. They exercise the _predicate
congruence_ fragment of equality — exactly the place where Leibniz expansion
**should** be cheap (a single propositional instantiation `P := λz. Q(z)`),
yet the prover still has to discover that binding.

**Single rewrite under a unary predicate.**

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      thf(a, type, a: $i).
      thf(b, type, b: $i).
      thf(p, type, p: $i>$o).
      thf(eq, axiom, a = b).
      thf(pa, axiom, p @ a).
      thf(conj, conjecture, p @ b).
      """,
      opts
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

