## Disequality and forcing closure

Reverse-direction problems: given equality assumptions, derive a contradiction
from a disequality. These should be discharged by a single clash after a
paramodulation step.

**Trivial forced clash.**

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      thf(a, type, a: $i).
      thf(b, type, b: $i).
      thf(c, type, c: $i).
      thf(e1, axiom, a = b).
      thf(e2, axiom, b = c).
      thf(ne, axiom, a != c).
      thf(conj, conjecture, $false).
      """,
      opts
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

