**Commutator of squares in an abelian group.** Pure equational reasoning over
a commutative group; the conjecture is trivial once commutativity is recognised
but visiting it should highlight the paramodulation/Leibniz gap on commuting
rewrites.

```elixir
race(
  fn opts ->
    prove(
      ~p"""
      #{group_axioms}
      thf(comm, axiom, ![X:$i, Y:$i]: o @ X @ Y = o @ Y @ X).
      thf(conj, conjecture,
        ![X:$i, Y:$i]:
          o @ (o @ X @ X) @ (o @ Y @ Y) = o @ (o @ X @ Y) @ (o @ X @ Y)).
      """,
      Keyword.put(opts, :timeout, 15_000)
    )
  end,
  configs
)
```

